Redescription. Body of male (
Fig. 73
) strongly convex, elongate and slender, with long appendages, BL 2.80–2.95 mm (mean 2.87 mm ); cuticle glossy, uniformly dark brown with slightly reddish hue, vestiture reddishbrown.

Pronotum (
Fig. 73
) in dorsal view strongly elongate, broadest near anterior third, PL 0.78–0.85 mm , (mean 0.80 mm ), PW 0.58–0.63 mm (mean 0.60 mm ); anterior and lateral margins in anterior half rounded; sides slightly concave in posterior third; posterior margin distinctly bisinuate; base of pronotum with two pairs of large and deep pits, additionally with a pair of shallow but distinct impressions located dorsolaterally. Punctures on pronotal disc fine and inconspicuous; entire dorsal and lateral surface of pronotum covered with moderately dense bristles, dorsally with admixture of thin setae.

Legs (
Fig. 73
) long and slender, without modifications.
